1
00:00:04,253 --> 00:00:07,665
Mahāprabhu in the mood 
of a devotee,

2
00:00:07,665 --> 00:00:10,154
He’s relishing this 
devotional position.

3
00:00:10,154 --> 00:00:13,794
As we’ve told recently 
with the Khirachora Gopīnāth,

4
00:00:13,794 --> 00:00:15,381
it’s mentioned,
when Mahāprabhu

5
00:00:15,381 --> 00:00:18,741
was telling the story 
of Mādhavendra Purī there …

6
00:00:18,741 --> 00:00:23,038
When the pūjārī brings the khir

7
00:00:23,038 --> 00:00:26,625
to Mahāprabhu, and Nityānanda Prabhu,
and His group,

8
00:00:26,625 --> 00:00:30,713
it’s mentioned there, that Mahāprabhu 
tasted this before as Gopīnāth.

9
00:00:30,903 --> 00:00:34,298
[A Most Wonderful Thing]

10
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:38,241
He’s also Kṛṣṇa, 
so He’s already taken it.

11
00:00:38,241 --> 00:00:41,084
So is this redundant?

12
00:00:41,084 --> 00:00:47,030
No. Because now He’s going 
to taste prasādam,

13
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:49,256
that’s what He wants to do.

14
00:00:49,256 --> 00:00:52,212
And He is telling us 
by these pastimes,

15
00:00:52,212 --> 00:00:56,642
that the position of the devotee—
that’s a greater taste,

16
00:00:56,642 --> 00:01:00,736
that’s a greater position to be in
than Kṛṣṇa.

17
00:01:00,736 --> 00:01:05,170
And only He can say that,
because He’s Kṛṣṇa.

18
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:10,941
If He wasn’t Kṛṣṇa, 
we might doubt it.

19
00:01:10,941 --> 00:01:13,821
We could say, “Well …”

20
00:01:17,606 --> 00:01:20,009
But He’s Kṛṣṇa, 
and He’s saying, 
 

21
00:01:20,009 --> 00:01:24,289
“Take it from Me, Kṛṣṇa, 
the Supreme Enjoyer,

22
00:01:24,289 --> 00:01:26,411
that the position 
of the devotee, 
 

23
00:01:26,411 --> 00:01:31,085
particularly the highest devotee—
Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī,

24
00:01:31,085 --> 00:01:34,955
is greater, it’s a more 
wonderful thing.”

